{"lemma":"جِيرُ","slug":"جِيرُ","root":"ج.#.ر","root_slug":"ج-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6810","n6811","n6812"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chalk, lime"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to plaster with chalk or lime"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to endorse, to make an assignment"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic גִיר / ܓܝܪ (gīr), from Akkadian 𒌋𒀜 (kīrum, “kiln”), from Sumerian 𒌋𒀜 (gir, “lime kiln”).\n\nDenominal verb of جِير (jīr, “chalk, lime”).\n\nDenominal verb of جِيرُو (jīrō, “endorsement”) for Italian girare.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6810","headword_ar":"جيّر","root":"jyr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He plastered"},{"kind":"text","text":"a watering-trough or tank"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jay~aAr","text_ar":"جَيَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6811","headword_ar":"جَيْرِ","root":"jyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mughnee, K, &c.,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosi","text_ar":"اَمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mughnee;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayora","text_ar":"جَيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayona","text_ar":"اَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayorK","text_ar":"جَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mughnee, K;) or this, where it occurs, is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayori A_in~a","text_ar":"جَيْرِ اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is properly written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayorino","text_ar":"جَيْرِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo","text_ar":"نَعَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a corroborative of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayori","text_ar":"جَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and its hemzeh and sheddeh and final vowel being here suppressed: (Mughnee:) a form of oath, (S, K,) or put in the place of an oath, (IAmb, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~FA","text_ar":"حَقًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or a responsive particle, (Mughnee,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo","text_ar":"نَعَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is most approved as responsive to an interrogation], (Mughnee, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalo","text_ar":"اَجَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is most approved as responsive to an affirmation]; (Sharh et-Tesheel, K;) not a noun in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~FA","text_ar":"حَقًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", for were it so it would be an inf. n.; nor in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadFA","text_ar":"اَبَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", for were it so it would be an adv. n. of time; and if it were a noun it would be decl., and would admit the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", and would not have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a corroborative, nor have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA","text_ar":"لَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to it, as it has in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA taquwlu laA A@bonapu AlEujayori\n                      \n                     \n                        taSoduqu laA A_i*aA taquwlu jayori"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the daughter of El-'Ojeyr says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she speaks truly: not when she says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jyr","text_ar":"جير"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mughnee:) or it is a verbal noun, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEorifu","text_ar":"اَعْرِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as is mentioned by Ibn-Abi-r-Rabeea, and by Er-Radee on the authority of 'Abd-El- Káhir. (MF.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayori laA A=tiyka","text_ar":"جَيْرِ لَا ا=تِيكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayori laA A^afoEalu *`lika","text_ar":"جَيْرِ لَا اَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA jayori laA A^afoEalu","text_ar":"لَا جَيْرِ لَا اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No, verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"[that]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","IAmb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n6812","headword_ar":"جِيرٌ","root":"jyr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gypsum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiS~N","text_ar":"جِصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) [In modern Arabic,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lime:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also what next follows.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}